title: Purdue falls to 1-6 with loss at Wisconsin
text:
Purdue falls to 1-6 with loss at Wisconsin 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive Purdue University Boilermakers October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 9:42 PM EDT 
MADISON, Wis. (21 Alive) - Alec Ingold scored two short yardage touchdowns and Wisconsin added to Purdue football's woes with a 24-7 win over the Boilermakers on Saturday. 
Purdue, now 1-6 got their only score on a two yard run by David Blough in the second quarter.
